name: Mario Wittmann
bio:
It’s almost impossible you’ve missed this, Instagram is the new hype of 2018. Everyone is talking about those so called “influencers” nowadays, they’re the ones who change the world. Based on what they wear, use, do and share on their social media they influent teens and other Instagram users. 

On Instagram, we’ve got the famous huge influencers with 1 million followers, but we also got smaller influencers which remain undiscovered. That’s why we’re writing this blogpost, today we want to introduce you to one of our recently discovered accounts: @fistofbuddha, a so called “new kid on the block”, if we’re talking about amazing undiscovered influencers you should know about then there’s no way you can miss out on this one. 

Mario posts high quality variating content every day, Mario really interacts with followers by asking their opinion on daily stuff making you as a follower feel more connected to the account. So far Mario managed to grow the following of the account to over 33368 already, an impressive amount in such a short timespan!

Today, if you want to get in touch with this so called “influencers” and have them promote your brand, most people will think of accounts with 100,000 followers or more. They will go to the biggest names in the industry, and understandably so. The more powerful an influencer is, the more valuable their promotion will have. But as competition for the big influencers begins to grow we’ll likely see more diversity among influencer targets and see smaller influencers popup. In other words, we’ll see influencers of all levels, including the high-follower elite and low-follower newcomers like Mario, getting attention from brands. 

The other big shift that we’re going to see is a more active approach to our otherwise passive social profiles. What I mean by this is that, right now, our social accounts, Twitter profiles, Instagram and Facebook accounts are all passive representations of our actual personality, aspirations, thoughts, feelings. But the platform itself does not actually engage with the user on the other side. It doesn’t talk back when someone interacts with it. That’s something Mario is doing really well, really engaging with the followers on the account.

name: Hashtag Family Travel
bio:
We’re a family of five (Bill, Amber, Will, Thomas, & Lucas) on a journey to find, experience and curate the best family travel adventures from our own backyard to around the world. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 
When we started having kids, we began to think about the experiences we wanted to give our family. We wanted our kids to see how big the world truly is, experience all different kinds of cultures and people, and realize how great it all is. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀ 
We only had one problem - we had no idea where to start. That’s where a little fate and coincidence came into play. Amber, quite randomly, was asked to become a travel agent. And suddenly we began to discover many of the destinations we never thought possible, could in fact be possible with a little knowledge and planning. 
We have a hunch a lot of you probably feel the way we did. We want to show you and help you realize if we can do it, you can too. 

We’re glad you’re here and we hope you’ll follow our journey! Once you take that first adventure, if you’re like us, it won’t be the last.

name: Marli Average Girl Traveler
bio:
Hello! 
My name is Marli. I'm a 30+ years young woman that discovered love for travelling the world later than most. I'm an introvert, shy person who doesn't have many friends so these where my walls to get over. Eventually, I slowly started looking at all-inclusive vacations and exploring Caribbean. After getting accustomed to it, I wanted to try something different. I found a very cheap flight to Dublin for two weeks and bought it. Panic mode started: What now? Where to go? Where to sleep? What am I supposed to do? All those questions came at once. Good thing hubby is always there when I need him. We managed to come up with a trip through Europe. We both loved it! We decided to do it again! This time, we went on our way to Egypt. What an adventure it was! Shortly after it, we ended up planning a trip around Baltic Sea. We discovered a completely different side of Europe! Now, I’m planning to travel through Caucasus region and Balkans. I'm still to get the courage to travel on my own...
